cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically interpreting indoor scenes from RGBD images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves generating sets of potential object regions and transferring and aligning associated 3D models, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of a data-driven approach and the mention of visual reasoning suggest that the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper involves training models and encouraging fit to observations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with inferring physical models of objects and surfaces, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics).
